  <title><anchor xml:id="Icinga_addons" />&name-icinga; Addons</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">Introduction</emphasis></para>

  <para>There are a lot of "addon" software packages that are available for &name-icinga;. Addons can be used to extend &name-icinga;'s
  functionality or integrate &name-icinga; with other applications.</para>

  <para>Addons are available for:</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><anchor xml:id="addons-conf" />Managing the config files through a web interface</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-nconf;">&name-nconf;</link>, <link xlink:href="&url-nagiosql;">&name-nagiosql;</link>, 
          <link xlink:href="&url-lconf-en;">&name-lconf;</link>, <link xlink:href="&url-lilac;">&name-lilac;</link>, ...</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><anchor xml:id="addons-mon" />Monitoring remote hosts (*NIX, Windows, etc.)</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="nsca">&name-nsca;</link>, <link linkend="nrpe">&name-nrpe;</link>, <link xlink:href="&url-check_mk;">&name-check_mk;</link>, ...</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-nsclient;">&name-nsclient;</link>, ...</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para>Submitting passive checks from remote hosts</para>
      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-nsclient;">&name-nsclient;</link>, <link xlink:href="&url-check_mk;">&name-check_mk;</link>, ...</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><anchor xml:id="addons-logic" />Simplifying/extending the notification logic</para>
      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-bp;">&name-bp;</link> ...</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><anchor xml:id="addons-vis" />Visualizing the information</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-pnp-en;">&name-pnp;</link></para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-nagvis;">&name-nagvis;</link></para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><anchor xml:id="addons-web" />Alternative web interfaces</para>

      <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
          <para><link xlink:href="&url-thruk;">&name-thruk;</link>, <link xlink:href="&url-multisite;">&name-multisite;</link></para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para>...and much more</para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para>You can find many addons for &name-icinga; by visiting:</para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><link xlink:href="&url-nagios;">&name-nagios;.org</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link xlink:href="http://www.sourceforge.net">SourceForge.net</link></para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para><link xlink:href="&url-monitoringexchange;">&url-monitoringexchange;</link></para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para>First we'll give a brief introduction to a few of the addons that Ethan Galstad developed for &name-nagios;...</para>

  <para><anchor xml:id="addons-nrpe" /><emphasis role="bold">NRPE</emphasis></para>

  <para><inlinemediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="../images/nrpe.png" format="PNG"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para>&name-nrpe; is an addon that allows you to execute <link linkend="plugins">plugins</link> on remote Linux/Unix hosts. This is useful if you
  need to monitor local resources/attributes like disk usage, CPU load, memory usage, etc. on a remote host. Similiar functionality can be
  accomplished by using the <emphasis>check_by_ssh</emphasis> plugin, although it can impose a higher CPU load on the monitoring machine -
  especially if you are monitoring hundreds or thousands of hosts.</para>

  <para>The &name-nrpe; addon can be found at <link xlink:href="https://git.icinga.org/?p=icinga-nrpe.git">https://git.icinga.org/?p=icinga-nrpe.git</link>.
  You will find the <link linkend="nrpe">documentation</link> in the next section.</para>

  <para><anchor xml:id="addons-nsca" /><emphasis role="bold">&name-nsca;</emphasis></para>

  <para><inlinemediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="../images/nsca.png" format="PNG"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para>&name-nsca; is an addon that allows you to send <link linkend="passivechecks">passive check</link> results from remote Linux/Unix hosts to
  the &name-icinga; daemon running on the monitoring server. This is very useful in <link linkend="distributed">distributed</link> and <link
  linkend="redundancy">redundant/failover</link> monitoring setups.</para>

  <para>The &name-nsca; addon can be found at <link xlink:href="https://git.icinga.org/?p=icinga-nsca.git">https://git.icinga.org/?p=icinga-nsca.git</link>.
  You will find the <link linkend="nsca">documentation</link> in the next section.</para>

  <para><anchor xml:id="addons-idoutils" /><emphasis role="bold">IDOUtils</emphasis></para>

  <para><inlinemediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="../images/idoutils.png" format="PNG"></imagedata>
      </imageobject>
    </inlinemediaobject></para>

  <para>IDOUtils is an addon that allows you to store all status information from &name-icinga; in a database. Multiple instances of
  &name-icinga; can all store their information in a central database for centralized reporting. In the future it will probably be used as a
  basis for a &name-php; based web interface.</para>

  <para>The IDOUtils addon install instructions can be found in the <link linkend="quickstart-idoutils">Quickstart-Idoutils</link> and more
  documentation can be found at <link xlink:href="http://docs.icinga.org/latest/en/">&url-icingadocs;</link>.</para>

